# Cursor Rules for NotesMagic Development

## Scope Limitation
- ONLY modify the files specified in this PR
- DO NOT touch any other files unless explicitly requested
- Stay within the defined scope of the current task

## File Modification Rules
- Make minimal, focused changes
- Follow existing code patterns and architecture
- Preserve the modular Swift Package structure
- Maintain SwiftUI best practices

## Architecture Constraints
- Keep changes within the specified package boundaries
- Follow the established protocol-based architecture
- Maintain separation between Domain, Data, and Features layers
- Preserve existing import statements and dependencies

## Code Quality
- Use Swift 5.10+ syntax
- Follow Apple HIG for UI components
- Maintain consistent naming conventions
- Add appropriate documentation for new functionality

## Testing
- Ensure changes compile without errors
- Maintain existing functionality
- Consider impact on other components
